    "value": "Regulation (EU) 2024/2847, known as the Cyber Resilience Act (CRA), is a significant European Union law focused on horizontal cybersecurity requirements for products with digital elements, like connected hardware and software. It aims to ensure that such products are secure throughout their lifecycle, reduce vulnerabilities, and harmonize cybersecurity standards across the EU【3:0†source】【3:2†source】【3:7†source】.\n\nHowever, your query specifically requests \"ANNEX VII\" of Regulation 32024R2847 (the official citation for the CRA). Based on search results from EUR-Lex, the official European law database, and related compliance resources, the full regulatory text (including annexes) is available, but the exact content of \"ANNEX VII\" in the context of Regulation 2024/2847 is not directly quoted in the top available online resources. Instead, much of the public documentation and summaries focus on the main articles and first annexes (which usually detail product classes, requirements, or technical documentation).\n\nIf your request concerns another domain (such as medical devices, waste, chemicals, etc.), ANNEX VII serves different functions depending on regulation—such as requirements for notified bodies for medical devices, documentation for waste shipments, or test lists for chemical safety—but these are not directly related to the CRA.\n\n**To access ANNEX VII of Regulation (EU) 2024/2847 (Cyber Resilience Act):**\n- Visit the EUR-Lex official page for the regulation: [EUR-Lex Regulation 2024/2847](https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2024/2847/oj/eng)【3:0†source】.\n- Download the full regulation (PDF or HTML). Scroll to Annex VII, which will be found in the latter part of the document after the main articles and previous annexes.\n\n**Summary of what you can expect in ANNEX VII (in CRA context):**\nWhile not explicitly listed in public summaries, ANNEX VII in EU cybersecurity regulations typically contains:\n- A template for the EU declaration of conformity,\n- Details on documentation required for compliance,\n- Administrative information for manufacturers and authorities.\n\n**If you need the word-for-word text of ANNEX VII:**\nThe only way to ensure precise legal accuracy is to download the regulation from the official EUR-Lex source and extract ANNEX VII from the official document【3:0†source】.\n\nLet me know if you need help interpreting or summarizing the legal text once you've accessed the annex from EUR-Lex!",
